cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the study of deep learning models, their training process, interpretation, generalization error, and robustness to adversarial attacks. Additionally, the paper provides mathematical tools to investigate the surfaces that define the decision boundaries of these models. 

The paper also deals with computer vision (cs.CV) as it discusses the computational practices used for finding adversarial examples and computing the closest point on the decision boundary. 

Furthermore, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with the decision-making process of trained models. 

The paper also relates to neural networks (cs.NE) as it investigates the decision boundaries of trained neural networks. 

Finally, the paper involves cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it discusses the vulnerability of a model against adversarial attack and proposes improvements in the computational practices used for finding adversarial examples.
